title: 6,100 Home Plans
description:
6,100 Home Plans

Plans to build your own house


Please be sure you read the article called "Your Worst Mistake".
That article helps people who are shopping for a home. You read
that article by clicking on the HELP tab in the Home-Plan
Finder(TM) 2.0 application.
 
The help also has useful information for people who sell, build
or design homes. See the document called "Getting Down To
Business" found in the Help.

If you have trouble installing or running the software, see the
"Problems and Solutions" section in the "abbisoft.hlp" Help file.
To read the Help file, press F1 after starting the application.

You need to shut down all other programs before running the
install. Other programs might be using files we need to update.
If you experience installation problems, try shutting down all
other programs and then re-install this software.


When you attempt to install from your CD-ROM drive, you may 
receive this error message:

  ISSET_SE Caused a General Protection Fault in Module...

This behavior can occur if any of the following conditions 
exists: 

  Norton AntiVirus version 4.04 is installed and Norton 
  AutoProtect is enabled. 

  You use LiveUpdate for Norton AntiVirus to download an 
  updated version of Norton AntiVirus. 

  Microsoft IntelliPoint software is installed on your 
  computer, and the Point32 program is currently running. 

  Microsoft IntelliMouse or Microsoft IntelliMouse Trackball 
  software is installed on your computer, and the Mswheel 
  program is currently running. 

RESOLUTION
To work around this behavior, use the appropriate method
below, and then attempt to install this software again. 

  Norton AutoProtect Is Enabled
  Disable Norton AutoProtect Mode. To do so, right-click 
  the Norton icon on the taskbar, and then click Disable. 
  Disabling the Load AutoProtect At Startup option on the 
  AutoProtect tab does not disable AutoProtect. 

  You Use LiveUpdate to Download Norton AntiVirus
  Obtain the latest version of LiveUpdate for Norton AntiVirus 
  from Symantec&#039;s Web site. For more information about how to 
  obtain LiveUpdate, contact Symantec Technical Support. 

  The Point32 Program Is Running
  Quit the Point32 program by pressing CTRL+ALT+DELETE to 
  open the Close Program dialog box, clicking Point32, 
  clicking End Task, and then clicking End Task again. 

  The Mswheel Program Is Running
  Quit the Mswheel program by pressing CTRL+ALT+DELETE to 
  open the Close Program dialog box, clicking Mswheel, 
  clicking End Task, and then clicking End Task again. 

MORE INFORMATION

Norton AntiVirus, Point32, and Mswheel are manufactured by 
vendors independent of AbbiSoft Multimedia, Inc.; we make 
no warranty, implied or otherwise, regarding these products&#039; 
performance or reliability. 

MANUAL INSTALL

If you still have problems with the setup program, all of the
application files are located on the CD-ROM in the INSTALL
directory.  You can copy all of these files to a directory on
your harddrive, then run "abbisoft.exe". It is preferable
to do the copy in DOS, because Window&#039;s Explorer might hide
some of the files.

ADDITIONAL HELP

For additional help, go to the technical support internet
site at www.abbisoft.com/tech
